#Text=Cheney meets with Israeli and Palestinian leaders
#Text=Sunday , March 23 , 2008
#Text=United States Vice President Dick Cheney met with Israeli and Palestinian leaders on Sunday .

#Text=Cheney met with Israeli President Shimon Peres and Primer Minister Ehud Olmert and their Palestinian counterparts , the moderate President Mahmoud Abbas and Prime Minister Salam Fayyad as part of a tour of the Middle East .
#Text=Cheney told Palestinians that continuing violence against ill damage efforts for a Palestinian state .
#Text=Cheney noted " Terror and rockets do not merely kill innocent civilians , they also kill the legitimate hopes and aspirations of the Palestinian people . "
#Text=The Vice President remarked he is committed towards a Palestinian state , quoting President George W. Bush , " The establishment of the state of Palestine is long overdue .

column1: #Text=Terror and rockets do not merely kill innocent civilians , they also kill the legitimate hopes and aspirations of the Palestinian people . — U.S. Vice President Dick Cheney
#Text=Abbas condemned rocket attacks against Israel from the Hamas-controlled Gaza Strip , but also told Israel to ease their restrictions on Palestinians .
#Text=He also noted that Israel needs to stop building settlements within the West Bank .

#Text=Abbas noted that , " Peace and stability will not be achieved through a settlement expansion , or the setting up of checkpoints around towns and villages , and the military escalation against Gaza , nor the incursions , continuous incursions into West Bank villages and towns . "
#Text=Cheney met earlier in the day with Shimon Peres , the Israeli president .
#Text=Both men spoke of Iran , with Peres noting upfront that Iran and their leader Mahmoud Ahmadinejad wants to " build their two satellites -- the Hezbollah in Lebanon , and the Hamas in Gaza ...

#Text=Nobody can console us and say that the declarations of Ahmadinejad are less serious than they are ; we have to take it seriously , out of experience .

_	_	_	_

#Text=Cheney noted that the Bush administration is pledged to the peace process and also referenced Iran but not directly ,  We 're obviously dedicated to doing all we can as an administration to try to move the peace process forward , and also obviously actively involved in dealing with the threats that we see emerging in the region -- not only threats to Israel , but threats to the United States , as well . "

column1: #Text=Cheney met with Prime Minister Olmert on Saturday and told Olmert that , " The United States will never pressure Israel to take steps that threaten its security . "

#Text=He also told Olmert that the United States backs Israel 's right to defend itself from Hamas rocket attacks but that America was also working for a peace deal between Israel and the moderate Fatah-controlled Palestinian government in the West Bank .
#Text=Abbas lost control of the Gaza Strip to the rival Hamas party last year .
#Text=Abbas , who is the leader of the more moderate Fatah party currently runs the Palestinian government located in the West Bank , the other Palestinian territory .
